the **708 TFLOPS** compute-bound peak reference on Trace 1.\n**Action**: Investigate DNN library algorithm selection, tuning knobs, and execution configuration so Trace 1 reaches throughput closer to Trace 2 on this bf16 3×3 forward convolution without relying on layout changes.\n**Impact**: ~1.2–1.6 ms savings (60.0–80.0% of E2E)\n\n## Detailed Analysis\n\n<!-- reasoning-candidate tier=compute rank=1 -->\n#### Trace 1 convolution kernel time and TFLOPS lag Trace 2\n**Identification:** A single compute-bound convolution dominates Trace 1 kernel time in this category and shows a large gap to the precision-aware peak TFLOPS reference, while paired Trace 2 kernels finish much sooner for the same matched op (source: `convolution_metrics.json` → `operations[].time_ms`, `operations[].efficiency.tflops_achieved`, `operations[].efficiency.resolved_peak_maf`, `operations[].efficiency.bound_type`; `convolution_ops.csv` → `lca_total_kernel_time_trace2_us`, `delta_us (trace2 - trace1)`).\n\n**Data:**\n\n| Metric | Value | Flagged |\n|--------|-------|---------|\n| Trace 1 kernel time (ms) | 2.0 | Yes |\n| Trace 2 kernel time (ms) | 0.4 | — |\n| Difference (ms), trace2 − trace1 | -1.6 | — |\n| Achieved TFLOPS (T1) | 14.8 | Yes |\n| Peak reference TFLOPS (`resolved_peak_maf`, T1) | 708 | — |\n| Bound type (T1) | compute-bound | — |\n\n**Reasoning for Slowdown:** Trace 1 spends roughly **1.6 ms** more GPU kernel time than Trace 2 on this convolution. Trace 2 completes the same matched work in about one-fifth of Trace 1’s kernel duration. On Trace 1 the operation is compute-bound with high arithmetic intensity, yet sustained throughput stays near **14.8 TFLOPS** compared with the **708 TFLOPS** peak reference for matrix bf16.\n\n**Resolution:** Improving kernel mapping and tuning for this convolution reduces time without introducing transpose-heavy layout conversions, because transpose overhead is negligible in these metrics.\n\n**Impact estimate:**\n- Low end (75% gap target): 1.2 ms savings (60.0% E2E)\n- High end (100% gap target): 1.6 ms savings (80.0% E2E)\n- Range: 1.2–1.6 ms (60.0–80.0% E2E)\n","isEmpty":false,"exceededLimit":false,"totalLines":61,"fileSize":3726,"path":"/home/AMD/khoffmey/dev/TraceLens/evals/unit_tests_comparative/test06_conv_gap_exceeds_roofline/analysis_output_ref/category_findings/convolution_findings.md","readRange":{"startLine":1,"endLine":61},"relatedCursorRulePaths":[],"relatedCursorRules":[]}}}}},{"toolCall":{"shellToolCall":{"args":{"command":"cd /home/AMD/khoffmey/dev/TraceLens && python3 -c \"from TraceLens.AgenticMode.Standalone.utils.report_utils import write_impact_estimates; write_impact_estimates('/home/AMD/khoffmey/dev/TraceLens/evals/unit_tests_comparative/test06_conv_gap_exceeds_roofline/analysis_output_ref', 'convolution', 'compute')\"","workingDirectory":"","timeout":30000,"toolCallId":"tool_5dacc2d6-542f-4ac0-95db-de7c5b519db","simpleCommands":["cd","python3"],"hasInputRedirect":false,"hasOutputRedirect":false,"parsingResult":{"parsingFailed":false,"executableCommands":[{"name":"cd","args":[{"type":"word","value":"/home/AMD/khoffmey/dev/TraceLens"}],"fullText":"cd /home/AMD/khoffmey/dev/TraceLens"},{"name":"python3","args":[{"type":"word","value":"-c"},{"type":"string","value":"\"from TraceLens.AgenticMode.Standalone.utils.report_utils import write_impact_estimates; write_impact_estimates('/home/AMD/khoffmey/dev/TraceLens/evals/unit_tests_comparative/test06_conv_gap_exceeds_roofline/analysis_output_ref', 'convolution', 'compute')\""}],"fullText":"python3 -c \"from TraceLens.AgenticMode.Standalone.utils.report_utils import write_impact_estimates; write_impact_estimates('/home/AMD/khoffmey/dev/TraceLens/evals/unit_tests_comparative/test06_conv_gap_exceeds_roofline/analysis_output_ref', 'convolution', 'compute')\""}],"hasRedirects":false,"hasCommandSubstitution":false},"fileOutputThresholdBytes":"40000","isBackground":false,"skipApproval":false,"timeoutBehavior":"TIMEOUT_BEHAVIOR_BACKGROUND","hardTi