{"type":"tool_call","subtype":"completed","call_id":"toolu_bdrk_01DVp2AkCqF5cKgwAtYq25oh","tool_call":{"readToolCall":{"args":{"path":"/home/AMD/khoffmey/dev/TraceLens/evals/unit_tests_comparative/test06_conv_gap_exceeds_roofline/analysis_output_ref/category_findings/convolution_findings.md"},"result":{"success":{"content":"<!--\nCopyright (c) 2024 - 2025 Advanced Micro Devices, Inc. All rights reserved.\n\nSee LICENSE for license information.\n-->\n\n# Convolution Analysis\n\n**Status:** SUCCESS  \n**comparison_scope:** comparative  \n**Platform:** MI300X  \n\n## Overview\n\nConvolution category GPU kernel time totals **2.0 ms** on Trace 1 (**100%** of category kernel time). One operation, **`aten::convolution`**, accounts for the entire slice. Semantically this is a **standard 2D** convolution (bf16, 3×3 weights, activations `(4, 256, 56, 56)`). **`category_specific.transpose_overhead_percent`** is **0%**, so transpose-driven layout mismatch is not a signal here.\n\n## Operations Breakdown (kernel time)\n\n| Operation | Trace 1 Time (ms) | Trace 2 Time (ms) | Count (T1/T2) | Difference (ms) | FLOPS/Byte (T1) | Bound (T1) |\n|-----------|-------------------|-------------------|---------------|-----------------|-----------------|------------|\n| aten::convolution | 2.0 | 0.04 | 1 / 1 | -1.96 | 1368.67 | compute-bound |\n\nOn Trace 1 this op achieves about **14.8 TFLOPS** versus **`efficiency.resolved_peak_maf`** **708 TFLOPS** for the matching compute-bound peak (`matrix_bf16`). Trace 2’s matched kernels complete in **40 μs**.\n\n## Key Bottlenecks\n\n- **`aten::convolution`**: Comparative kernel time strongly favors Trace 2. Trace 1 remains far below the **708 TFLOPS** peak reference despite high arithmetic intensity, so closing the Trace 1 versus Trace 2 gap is the priority.\n\n## Recommendations\n\n### P1: Trace 1 convolution is much slower than Trace 2\n**Insight**: For the matched **standard 2D** convolution, Trace 1 spends about **2.0 ms** of GPU kernel time while Trace 2 finishes in about **0.04 ms**, and Trace 1 sustains roughly **14.8 TFLOPS** versus **708 TFLOPS** at the bf16 compute peak reference on Trace 1.\n\n**Action**: Align DNN library algorithm selection, fusion context, and execution configuration with Trace 2 for this bf16 3×3 convolution so Trace 1 approaches Trace 2 kernel duration; profile which forward path and workspace settings Trace 2 uses for the same signature.\n\n**Impact**: ~1.469–1.958 ms savings (73.43–97.91% of E2E)\n\n## Detailed Analysis\n\n<!-- reasoning-candidate tier=compute rank=1 -->\n#### Trace 1 convolution kernel time lags Trace 2\n**Identification:** The only convolution in this category is compute-bound on Trace 1 and consumes all category kernel time, while the matched Trace 2 run finishes orders of magnitude faster for the same op (source: `convolution_metrics.json` → `operations[].time_ms`, `operations[].efficiency.tflops_achieved`, `operations[].efficiency.resolved_peak_maf`, `operations[].efficiency.bound_type`; `convolution_ops.csv` → `lca_total_kernel_time_trace1_us`, `lca_total_kernel_time_trace2_us`, `delta_us (trace2 - trace1)`).\n\n**Data:**\n\n| Metric | Value | Flagged |\n|--------|-------|---------|\n| Trace 1 kernel time (ms) | 2.0 | Yes |\n| Trace 2 kernel time (ms) | 0.04 | — |\n| Difference (ms), trace2 − trace1 | -1.96 | — |\n| Achieved TFLOPS (T1) | 14.8 | Yes |\n| Peak reference TFLOPS (`resolved_peak_maf`, T1) | 708 | — |\n| Bound type (T1) | compute-bound | — |\n\n**Reasoning for Slowdown:** Trace 1 spends about **2.0 ms** on GPU kernels for this convolution while Trace 2 completes the matched work in about **40 μs** of kernel time. That is roughly **50×** more kernel duration on Trace 1 than on Trace 2 for the same op name and shape. On Trace 1 the workload is compute-bound at high **FLOPS/Byte**, yet sustained throughput stays near **14.8 TFLOPS** compared with the **708 TFLOPS** peak reference for matrix bf16.\n\n**Resolution:** Converging Trace 1 toward Trace 2’s execution path shortens the dominant kernel without relying on layout conversion, because measured transpose overhead is zero in this category. Matching how the library chooses the forward convolution implementation and associated workspace or dispatch options addresses the wall-clock gap directly.\n\n**Impact estimate:**\n- Low end (75% gap target): 1.469 ms savings (73.43% E2E)\n- High end (100% gap target): 1.958 ms savings (97.91% E2E)\n- Range: 1.469–1.958 ms (73.43–97.91% E2E)\n","isEmpty":false,"exceededLimit":false,"totalLines":63,"fileSize":4141,"path":"/home/AMD/khoffmey/dev/TraceLens/evals/unit_tests_comparative/test06_conv_gap_exceeds_roofline/analysis_output_ref/category_findings/convolution_findings.md","readRange":{"startLine":1,"endLine":63},"relatedCursorRulePaths":[],"relatedCursorRules":[]}}}},"model_call_id":"f3657724-9c30-457f-812a-5c07f7300673-34-nzgw","session_id":"1415083f-2a1f-4988-abe9-6e5ae135413f","timestamp_ms":1777504726687}
